- Physical Development:
- Physical growth is slower
- By age 6 , the average weight is 21 kgs and the average height is 46 inches
- Skeletal and muscle development helps the child assume a more adult appearance.
- Legs and lower body tend to grow more rapidly
- Muscle Coordination:
- -Run
- -Climb
- -Move more freely
- Muscles of the fingers develop:
- -Write
- -Draw
- -Use a fork and knife
